cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.RO 

This paper is primarily focused on computer vision (CV) and machine learning (ML) techniques for face alignment in videos. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel approach for learning from large scale unlabeled videos, which involves generating auxiliary annotations. This aspect of the paper aligns with the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves the development of an efficient network module, which could be relevant to the sub-category of cs.MM (Multimedia). The paper also involves reasoning about spatial-temporal relationships, which could be relevant to the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.RO (Robotics).
